

    
       Today I finished reading  Catch-22  by Joseph Heller. The story is set during WWII on the fictional island of Pianosa, following the lives of a group of American soldiers. I really enjoyed the story and themes of the book and, most of all, the dialogue which was hilarious and cleverly woven together. Although it is lengthy and difficult to follow at times, the characters shine through and add an addictive touch. It is quite possibly my new favorite book.    
    
    
